=80=99s not allowed to tender. Also, though, Weinstein=E2=80=99s offer real=
ly=C2=A0<em>is=C2=A0</em>contingent on getting approval from Sculptor=E2=80=
=99s limited partners =E2=80=94=C2=A0the board is not wrong about that =E2=
=80=94=C2=A0and so even without the standstill he wouldn=E2=80=99t want to =
buy all of Sculptor only to find out that he couldn=E2=80=99t run its funds=
. He is not going to just unconditionally buy all the shares.</li>=09<li st=
yle=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">The shareholder vote: Even if Sculptor=E2=80=99=
s board ignores Weinstein and proceeds with the Rithm deal, it needs to sub=
mit the deal to a shareholder vote, and the deal can=E2=80=99t close unless=
