<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">We <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusin=
ess.com/click/32686879.258425/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL=
2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDktMTEvc29tZS1mbG9hdGluZy1yYXRlcy13b24tdC1mbG9hdD9jbXBp=
ZD1CQkQwOTEyMjNfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2x=
ldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMzA5MTImdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b85=
24a319a23cB1cd1accd" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=
=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bord=
er-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: so=
lid; background-color: #ccc;">  talked yesterday</a> about how the US Secur=
ities and Exchange Commission has allowed futures-based Bitcoin exchange-tr=
aded funds, but has so far blocked spot Bitcoin ETFs, but that will probabl=
y change after the SEC lost a court challenge brought by Grayscale Investme=
nts LLC. That means that there will probably soon be spot Bitcoin ETFs, whi=
ch will be simpler and cheaper than Bitcoin futures ETFs, so investors who =
want Bitcoin ETFs will probably switch. This is sad for the people who quit=
e cleverly invented Bitcoin futures ETFs as a way around the SEC=E2=80=99s =
opposition, and who will soon have a clever product that no one wants. Ther=
e is hope for them, though. I wrote:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If you run a Bitcoin futures ETF, =
and you see the spot Bitcoin ETFs coming for you, are you at least consider=
ing opening a 2x levered Bitcoin ETF? I=E2=80=99m sure the SEC would love t=
hat.</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Well, that last sentence was sarcastic. The SE=
C seems to me to be skeptical of all crypto; it kind of thinks that Bitcoin=
 is just gambling, which makes a 2x Bitcoin ETF double gambling. But a=C2=
=A0reader pointed out that <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.c=
om/click/32686879.258425/aHR0cHM6Ly92b2xhdGlsaXR5c2hhcmVzLmNvbS9iaXR4/607f0=
7ceef4b8524a319a23cB1c797a5f" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope=
" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !importa=
nt; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-s=
tyle: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> Volatility Shares already did this</=
a>, and the SEC approved it:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The 2x Bitcoin Strategy ETF (Ticke=
r: BITX) seeks to provide daily investment results, before fees and expense=
s, that correspond generally to twice the performance of the S&amp;P CME Bi=
tcoin Futures Daily Roll Index (Ticker: SPBTFDUE) for a single day, not for=
 any other period. The fund does not invest directly in bitcoin. Instead, t=
he Fund seeks to benefit from increases in the price of Bitcoin Futures Con=
tracts for a single day.</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The SEC doesn=E2=80=99t want to make it too ea=
sy to invest in Bitcoin via ETFs, but, due to its own odd logic, it has mad=
e it possible to invest in=C2=A0<em>double=C2=A0</em>Bitcoin via ETFs.=C2=
=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">By the way, as part of its legal challenge to =
the SEC, Grayscale <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click=
/32686879.258425/aHR0cHM6Ly9ncmF5c2NhbGUuY29tL3dwLWNvbnRlbnQvdXBsb2Fkcy8yMD=
IzLzA3L0dyYXlzY2FsZS0yOGotbGV0dGVyLXJlLTJ4LUJUQy1mdXR1cmVzLUVURi03LjcuMjMuc=
GRm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB794855d2" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"=
itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none=
 !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border=
-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">complained about this irony<=
/a> in a letter to the court:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The 2x Bitcoin Strategy ETF, which seeks to do=
uble the performance of the S&amp;P CME Bitcoin Futures Daily Roll Index ea=
ch day, is leveraged. As a result, it exposes investors to an even riskier =
investment product than traditional bitcoin futures exchange-traded product=
s (=E2=80=9CETPs=E2=80=9D), which encompass risks related to both the futur=
es and spot bitcoin markets. ...</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The fact that the Commission has allowed a lev=
eraged bitcoin futures ETP to=C2=A0begin trading demonstrates that the Comm=
ission continues to arbitrarily treat spot bitcoin ETPs differently than bi=
tcoin futures ETPs. =E2=80=A6 The 2x Bitcoin Strategy ETF is therefore expo=
sed to even more risks of the bitcoin markets than Grayscale=E2=80=99s prop=
osed spot bitcoin ETP.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If you worry about spot Bitcoin ETFs because y=
ou think the Bitcoin market is manipulated, well, a 2x Bitcoin ETF is twice=
 as manipulated.</p>
